headline.main: CHINESE BLOCK AID SENT TO OWCHIHKOW; Rescue Column Intercepted -- Garrison Near Collapse

lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, July 1 (U.P.) -- The Japanese, fighting desperately to save Owchihkow, one of their last footholds in the rich Tungting Lake region, have attempted to send reinforcements to their encircled forces there, but Chinese troops intercepted the rescue column, Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek's High Command announced tonight.
abstract: Chinese block Jap aid to Owchihkow garrison; reach 2 more points on Yangtze south bank northwest of Owchihkow; fighting reptd across river from Shasi; 3 Jap drives on Chinese positions south of Canton repelled; puppet units of 44th Nanking Div near Chaoan reptd to have joined Chungking forces
